<task id="AIPU2-063" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Per-Tool Error Isolation in ResolveTools</title>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, resilience</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-061</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    After AIPU2-061 moves tool resolution to CapabilityRouter, individual tool registrations can
    throw during resolution (missing configuration, failed capability check, transient dependency
    failure). Without isolation, one broken tool kills the entire tool set for the turn. Implement
    per-tool error isolation in the tool resolution path so that each tool is resolved in its own
    try-catch: failures return a typed error result recorded in the audit log, and remaining tools
    continue to resolve and execute normally.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with resilience pattern experience (try-catch isolation, structured logging).</role>
  <goal>
    One broken tool does not kill all tools. Failed tools produce an error result in the audit log
    and are excluded from the turn's tool set. Healthy tools are unaffected. Unit tests confirm
    partial-failure scenarios behave correctly.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/resilience.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read SprkChatAgentFactory.cs (post AIPU2-061) and resilience.md to understand the expected isolation pattern used elsewhere in the BFF.</step>
    <step>Wrap each individual tool resolution call in an isolated try-catch within the CapabilityRouter resolution loop.</step>
    <step>On catch: log the exception with tool name and turn correlation ID using the structured logger; return a ToolResolutionError record instead of throwing.</step>
    <step>Filter out ToolResolutionError entries before passing the tool list to ISprkAgent.ExecuteTurnAsync so only healthy tools reach the LLM.</step>
    <step>Write the list of failed tool names to the audit log entry for the turn (so operators can diagnose).</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: (a) all tools healthy — normal path unchanged; (b) one tool throws — others still resolve; (c) all tools throw — agent executes with empty tool list (no crash).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Each tool resolution is wrapped in an isolated try-catch — exception in one does not propagate to others.</criterion>
    <criterion>Failed tools are logged with tool name and correlation ID; excluded from the resolved tool list.</criterion>
    <criterion>Agent executes successfully even if all tools fail (empty tool list is valid input to ISprkAgent).</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests for partial-failure and total-failure scenarios pass.</criterion>
    <criterion>No changes to the resilience.md pattern contract — implementation follows established BFF conventions.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
